## Optimization

Activities exploring how to find the best solutions among many possibilities:

### Minimal Networks (Soap Film Computers)

Soap films naturally find minimal surfaces—the shortest network connecting points. These activities use soap films to solve optimization problems that challenge even modern computers!

- [Soap: 4-Point](CURRENT/soap_4point) — Find the shortest network connecting 4 points using soap film
- [Soap: 5-Point](CURRENT/soap_5point) — Explore minimal Steiner trees with 5 points
- [Soap: Grid](CURRENT/soap_grid) — Discover minimal networks on grid arrangements
- [Soap: Metro](CURRENT/soap_metro) — Optimize metro/subway network connections using soap films

### Graph Coloring

- [Solid Face Colouring](CURRENT/solid_face_coloring) — Color the faces of 3D solids with minimum colors so no adjacent faces match
- [Solid Edge Colouring](CURRENT/solid_edge_coloring) — Color the edges of 3D solids with minimum colors so no edges sharing a vertex match

