## Learning Objectives

By the end of this module, you will be able to:

* Understand what algorithms are and recognize them in everyday life
* Apply searching techniques like binary search to find items efficiently
* Use sorting algorithms to organize data systematically
* Solve puzzles through systematic exploration of possibilities
* Analyze games and develop winning strategies using algorithmic thinking
* Recognize the role of constraints in algorithm design
* Understand optimization problems and how nature finds minimal solutions
* Apply graph coloring concepts to real-world scheduling and mapping problems
* Create algorithmic art using mathematical rules and patterns
* Explore the connections between geometry, topology, and computation
